Copyright 2026 Tanvrit Private Limited and Smritidb contributors

This product includes software developed by the Smritidb project at
Tanvrit Private Limited.

The project name draws from the Sanskrit term *smriti* (स्मृति, "memory").
The mathematical substrate draws from research publications including:

  - Kanerva, P. (1988). Sparse Distributed Memory. MIT Press.
  - Plate, T. A. (1995). Holographic Reduced Representations.
    IEEE TNN 6(3), 623–641.
  - Kanerva, P. (2009). Hyperdimensional Computing.
    Cognitive Computation 1(2), 139–159.

These works are cited for prior art and intellectual lineage; the
implementations in this repository are not derivative works of them.

The Smritidb Memory Format (KMF) specification is licensed separately
under CC-BY-4.0 once the v1.0.0 specification freeze occurs;
until then it is distributed under the same Apache-2.0 license as
the reference implementations.

The reference implementations make use of:

  - @noble/hashes (MIT License) — synchronous BLAKE3 implementation.

Their respective licenses are reproduced in the NOTICE files distributed
with those packages.
